      "header": "Mobile Layout (FIXED Feb 2026)",
      "content": "## Mobile Layout (FIXED Feb 2026)\n- **Root cause**: React SPA in `client/src/` uses Tailwind — patching `public/*.html` had zero effect\n- **Fix (Feb 14)**: 12 files updated with responsive classes: 44px touch targets, 16px input font (iOS zoom prevention), grid-cols-2 base, bottom-sheet modals on mobile, horizontal scroll tabs, safe areas, overscroll containment\n- **Status**: LIVE; verified on 320px-1440px+ screens",
      "relevance": "83%"
    },
    {
      "layer": 3,
      "layer_name": "Cross-Company Patterns",
      "header": "Frontend Architecture & Responsive Design",
      "content": "### Frontend Architecture & Responsive Design\n- **Framework/build tool audit before responsive work**: Verify actual frontend architecture before applying fixes; check if React SPA (Vite/Webpack) in `client/` vs. static HTML in `public/`; fixes applied to wrong directory have zero effect on user-visible UI\n- **React + Tailwind as modern SPA stack**: Vite-bundled React app with Tailwind CSS for responsive design; responsive utilities (grid-cols-1, grid-cols-2, hidden md:block, text-sm md:text-base) replace media queries; all components must use Tailwind classes not inline styles for consistency\n- **Mobile-first responsive pattern in Tailwind**: Base classes apply to mobile (320px), then `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:` breakpoints override for larger screens; responsive grid pattern: `grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3` collapses cards from 3 → 2 → 1 column on smaller viewports\n- **Mobile hamburger + overlay architecture**: Detect viewport width via `window.matchMedia('(max-width: 768px)')`, inject hamburger button HTML + click handler that toggles overlay visibility; overlay covers full viewport with semi-transparent background; sidebar slides in/out on toggle; applies to 25+ dashboard/sidebar pages\n- **Responsive CSS coverage checklist**: iOS zoom prevention (`user-scalable=no` in viewport meta), grid collapse (2-column → 1-column <768px), touch targets minimum 44px, modal/table mobile fixes, support 320px-1440px+ widths; critical for consistent mobile UX across all pages\n- **iOS Safari zoom prevention on form focus**: Add `font-size: 16px` (minimum) on mobile input elements; iOS Safari",
      "relevance": "70%"
    },
    {
      "layer": 3,
      "layer_name": "Cross-Company Patterns",
      "header": "Current Cross-Company Patterns (engineering) (9247 tokens)",
      "content": "## Current Cross-Company Patterns (engineering) (9247 tokens)",
      "relevance": "27%"
    },
    {
      "layer": 2,
      "layer_name": "Company Context & Preferences",
      "header": "User Preferences & Communication Style",
      "content": "## User Preferences & Communication Style\n- **Agent task orchestration**: Semi-automated agent chaining — no waiting for approval between steps\n- **Bug fix testing flow**: Free retries on engineering fixes until fully resolved (no credit limits)\n- **Testing approach**: User manually tests, reports issues with specific details; prefers targeted questions to narrow down problems\n- **File writes**: Route .md documentation updates to engineering agent (data agent struggles with repo files)\n- **Documentation structure**: Keep CURRENT vs TARGET architecture files separate (not consolidated)\n- **Preference**: Working solutions over bug reports; provide fixes with available resources\n- **Model strategy**: Use available models from current stack; user sources new providers if needed\n- **Transparency**: Know upfront what models/resources are needed (don't discover gaps mid-task)\n- **Task communication**: Auto-queue next-step tasks when results available (no waiting to be asked)\n- **Quick Practice feedback clarity**: User feedback must include the candidate's transcribed answer text alongside scores/tips so users remember what they said\n- **Bug filing**: Accept bug reports with specific details; file tickets for engineering agent to investigate with logs/dashboards",
      "relevance": "25%"
    },
    {
      "layer": 1,
      "layer_name": "Domain Knowledge (This Company)",
      "header": "Chart Rendering Bugs (Feb 14)",
      "content": "## Chart Rendering Bugs (Feb 14)\n- **Hourly Usage chart empty**: CSS bug — intermediate wrapper div broke flex `height: XX%` resolution (0px bars). **Fix**: Removed wrapper, bars are now direct flex children\n- **Last 7 Days chart flat**: Today excluded + bars scaled against 100K budget (4% = 2px invisible). **Fix**: Include today as final bar, relative scaling (tallest = 100%), reconciliation cross-checks `ai_call_log` for missing historical data",
      "relevance": "15%"
    }
  ]
}

